3 Nov 2017 / 486 / 19

In the last week, 29 more cases are reported with 1 more death. More than a 1/3 of the cases had neither homelessness nor substance abuse risk factors. It is possible that subclinical hepatitis A in food handlers may be responsible for some of the cases with no clear risk factors. Recommending hepatitis A vaccination among food handlers, as done in San Diego County, should be a consideration in Michigan. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5426879,225.]
